WORKLET.DESCRIPTION:
This Worklet manages the load of the S_Survey, W_VS_Class, W_VS_Group, and W_VS_Loc tables.

WORKLET.DESCRIPTION:
PURPOSE This session worklet is responsible for loading the SYCO Promotion Transaction data file in staging table S_Promotion_Transaction. This staging table may then be used as the source for D_Comment, D_Promotion_Detail, W_Promotion, and F_Promotion_Transaction mappings.
PREDECESSORS None
SUCCESSORS wkl_Promotion_Comment wkl_Promotion_Details
NOTES Prior to loading the Staging Table, it must be truncated. The Staging table is necessary because Informatica does not provide any efficient means by which a Fact Upsert (insert or update) can be done when sourced from a file. In order to check for existence in the fact table, a joiner would want to read the entire target table, a cached lookup would copy the entire target table down to the Informatica Server, and uncached lookups are inexorably slow. The staging table permits us to join the source to the target efficiently on the database (in the Source Qualifier) prior to bringing the data down to Informatica.
WORKLET.NAME: wkl_Promotion_Staging
